    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1925-05-16T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1925-05-16T08:00:00-05:00" n="70"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d70">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.51 W 89Czeclioslovakia/92: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Czechoslovakia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Einstein</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Prague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-05-16T14:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 16, 1925—2 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 3:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. Your number 11, May 5, 4 p.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Doctor Beneš admitted that he had forgotten his letter of June 25 [<hi
                            rend="italic">26</hi>], 1919; if he had remembered this he would have
                        negotiated differently with Great Britain.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>He reaffirms the intention of Czechoslovakia to honor all her
                        engagements.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>On his return from Geneva where he goes tomorrow he will take up the debt
                        question with the Minister of Finance and give me early answer. My
                        impression is that he will settle relief bonds on the same terms as extended
                        to other governments.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Einstein</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
